Class DoublyLinkedList<E>

java.lang.Object
DoublyLinkedList<E>
public class DoublyLinkedList<E>
extends java.lang.Object
A partial implementation of lists using doubly linked elements, similar to that of java.util.LinkedList.

Doubly linked lists are less space-efficient than singly linked lists, but tail-related operations are less costly.

    • toStringReverse

      public java.lang.String toStringReverse()
      Construct a string representation of list, listing the elements in the reverse order separated by comma, e.g. "[0, 5, 3]". "[]" is returned for and empty list. The elements are retrieved from tail to head using the previous reference.

      A string representing elements of list in reverse order
